## Objective
Add vertical scroll to the content in the about page.

Current about: main aero-glass div with lots of content (header, paras, sections, live reactions, ko-fi). Inside Container which has min-h-[100dvh] overflow-y-auto flex... justify-between. On some viewports or with content, it may not scroll the inner content nicely, or user wants the about content to have its own scroll (e.g. max-h and overflow-y-auto on the glass div or a wrapper).

Fix: Wrap or style the main content div in about to support vertical scroll (e.g. max-h-[calc(100dvh-XXX)] overflow-y-auto), or make the inner sections scroll while header fixed. Ensure no layout break, preserve mt-16 etc for back button. Test on mobile/full.

## Constraints / Invariants
- Preserve aero-glass, fonts, animations, haptics on interactive parts (sparks).
- Do not introduce horizontal scroll.
- Minimal change, IIPS.
- After review gate.

## Verification
- Build succeeds.
- About page content scrolls vertically when tall (e.g. simulate long content or check on small height).
- Other pages unaffected.
- No h-scroll anywhere.
